<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">lemonade</ENAMEX>." You say <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">water</ENAMEX> would suffice. He says, "Oh, but lemonade is much
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">nicer</ENAMEX>. Here"--handing you a packet of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">lemonade powder</ENAMEX>--"just add <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">water</ENAMEX> and
